Name: Ras
CharDesc: Created to protect the world and all life within it, he is admired as the leader of the Heirs and the alter ego of the Goddess. He has a good personality and is very understanding, though he lacks some understanding of Humans.
SpecialtySkill_Desc: The Heir of the Covenant bears the weight of the world upon his shoulders.

Name: Cecilia
CharDesc: A brave woman known as the Storm Dragon Knight. Cecilia is Queen of Wintenberg and has a strong sense of responsibility. She has a righteous and sincere personality, but will stubbornly resist any attempts to change her mind.
SpecialtySkill_Desc: Having long fought dragons, the Wintenberg dynasty passes down their knowledge via holy scripture.

Name: Rose
CharDesc: A close aide of Cecilia's, Rose followed her all the way from Wintenberg. She loves to fight and has a good sense of humor. Her belief is that the strongest warrior die with no regrets.

Name: Silk
CharDesc: A young Elf born in Dun Blyraia, the Eternal Forest. At a young age Silk left the forest, meaning she knows little of her own race and her home. Her personality is bright and cheerful like a spring breeze.
SpecialtySkill_Desc: Maybe it sounds like wind, but it's really a song sent from the forest.

Name: Mercedes
CharDesc: A Homunculus placed in the care of Queen Diene some years previously, Mercedes has a poker face that gives away little emotion, but she grows quickly attached to those who show her kindness. Sometimes, she may awkwardly mimic others or repeat what they say.
SpecialtySkill_Desc: The Eye of Kal's knowledge came from the Goddess Diche.

Name: Kise
CharDesc: Leader of the Nocturnes. Having been forced to part with her lover, she now has a tendency to obsess over anything she loves.
SpecialtySkill_Desc: Even time stops in front of her will.

Name: Vildred
CharDesc: Due to his humorous style of speaking, many mistake Vildred as being light-hearted, but he has a serious side that leads him to stubbornly push ahead with what he thinks is right.
SpecialtySkill_Desc: Under his sword, every ill will is brought to light.

Name: Armin
CharDesc: A particularly ticklish feline Suin, Armin is the valiant and cheerful Commander of the Longtail Company. However, she is easily tempted, and quickly convinced to go along with the whims of her fellow mercenaries. She loves to collect earrings but since her ears are so sensitive she's unable to actually wear them.
SpecialtySkill_Desc: Handles requests with diligence and efficiency.

Name: Charlotte
CharDesc: Owner of La Mare, a castle in the Solayu Dark Swamp, Charlotte is known as the Lady of the Swamp. Fiercely competitive, she has a love-hate relationship with Cecilia. Full of pride, she despises anyone who points out her insecurities.
SpecialtySkill_Desc: From the swamp to the throne.

Name: Zerato
CharDesc: The frost mage of Reingar, Zerato is the second son of a Spirit Weaver clan, blessed by Nixied, the Lord of Winter. He's a genius who hates to feel hot, and loves showing off. Like most Reingar students he pays no attention to those things he deems unimportant, and often crosses the line in his study of magic.
SpecialtySkill_Desc: Gifted with natural talent and the blessing of Nixied, nobody can best him.

Name: Karin
CharDesc: Second Lieutenant in the Public Security Club of Reingar, Karin struggles to maintain order in the Magical Academy, a place brimming with dangerous creativity. Many call her the conscience and the real big boss of the Public Security Club.
SpecialtySkill_Desc: As Justice is the root of all order, she performs one heroic exploit after another.

Name: Corvus
CharDesc: A priest of the Rose Apostles, Corvus is famous in Farche for leading the Young Sheep of the Eternal Mother missionaries.
SpecialtySkill_Desc: Helps wanderers with sincerity and passion.

Name: Cartuja
CharDesc: In Farche, the nomadic Tuharta Clan is wiped out by a great sandstorm. Cartuja leads the few survivors as they wander in search of a new home, working day and night as a mercenary to raise enough money to save his clan.
SpecialtySkill_Desc: Their curiosity for the new world is second to none.

Name: Schuri
CharDesc: A master of gunpowder weaponry, Schuri has a strong sense of pride and arrogance, though suffers a complex about his weak physical strength.
SpecialtySkill_Desc: Sharp instincts separate truth from falsehood.

Name: Dingo
CharDesc: A genius holding the power of inferno in his hands after swearing a compact with Malicus, the Lord of Fire, Dingo became a chef to make full use of his abilities. He sees all living creatures as potential ingredients.
SpecialtySkill_Desc: Dingo's dishes are so good they'll make you hallucinate. A real chef's chef.

Name: Ruele of Light
CharDesc: An Heir of the Sixth World, Ruele is revered for her kindness. She is a Soul Weaver who gained the favor of the Lord of Light, Destina. Her only hobby is telling fortunes with rabbit fortune cookies.
SpecialtySkill_Desc: In her presence, even evil loses its darkness.

Name: Kayron
CharDesc: An Acolyte, and commander of an army of undead known as the Dust Walkers. It is said that he demands your soul and loyalty in return for releasing you from your grudges.
SpecialtySkill_Desc: He destroys everything with his army of Dust Walkers, yearning for the annihilation of the world.

Name: Iseria
CharDesc: Second-in-Command of the Order of the Sword, Iseria is an Elf unable to return to her ancestral home of Dun Blyraia due to some reason. Known as the Knight of White Flowers, she has a calm and solemn personality.
SpecialtySkill_Desc: Elves are always curious about new worlds.

Name: Charles
CharDesc: Although he may be rigid and loyal, he cannot help but act like an overprotective servant to Aither, and will deal with all kinds of things in order to protect him.
SpecialtySkill_Desc: He represented by a strong will and devotion to Ezera.
